
    <div class="content-floor">
      <span class="content-door">
        <a href="/">s</a>
      </span>
      <div class="content-anteroom">
        <h1>
          upaspy
        </h1>
        <p>
          Hi, so you want to check if your friend has visited some concrete www pages?
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="content-floor content-floor-active">
      <span class="content-door">
        1
      </span>
      <div class="content-anteroom">
        <p>
          Type url addresses of these pages and your email.
        </p>
      </div>
			<div class="content-sitting-room" id="content-1">
        <form method="POST" action="/create">
          <p class="url">
            <input type="text" name="urls[]" value="http://" class="url" maxlength="120"/>
          </p>
          <small class="hint">
            hit Enter for new url, remove with Backspace
          </small>
          <p>
            <input type="text" name="mail" value="your email" class="mail placeholder" />
          </p>
        </form>
			</div>
    </div>
    <div class="content-floor">
      <span class="content-door">
        2
      </span>
      <div class="content-anteroom">
        <p>
         A personalized supaspy link is generated for you.
         It can be used 3 times.
        </p>
        <p>
         Your friend has to visit the link. Then you will get results in your mailbox.
        </p>
      </div>
			<div class="content-sitting-room" id="content-2">
        <p>
          <a href="#" id="done" class="button">
            done<span class="ques">?</span><span class="excl">!</span>
            generate the link
          </a>
        </p>
			</div>
